# Player OS dashboard

## Layout (OperativeHub)

`HUDContainer` wraps the dashboard shell. Inside `OperativeHub`:

| Zone | Grid span | Component |
|------|-----------|-----------|
| Identity | `bento-span-4` | `IdentityBentoModule` |
| Metrics | `bento-span-8` | `HudMetricsPanel` |
| Quests / missions | `bento-span-12` | `ActiveBounties` |

Below the hub row: `VanguardProtocolPanel` and memory capsules as documented in [`docs/vision/PLAYER_OS.md`](../../docs/vision/PLAYER_OS.md).

**Route shell:** `src/routes/(app)/player/dashboard/+page.svelte`

## Components (do not rename)

- `IdentityBentoModule` — operative identity, avatar, rank
- `HudMetricsPanel` — streak, XP, telemetry readouts
- `ActiveBounties` — mission list (use `deduplicateById` for dedup)
- `VanguardProtocolPanel` — protocol / compliance capsule
- `HUDContainer` — shared HUD chrome from `src/lib/components/hud/HUDContainer.svelte`

## CSS

Primary stylesheet: `src/lib/styles/player-dashboard-hud.css`

Player OS uses **chamfered corners** (`clip-path`), not `border-radius`. Tokens: see `.cursorrules` (`#0f172a`, `#334155`, `#fbbf24`).

